  "texts": [
    "A general trend in AI educational research is a preference towards quantitative (80%) and theoretical or descriptive papers (17%) over qualitative (2%) or mixed methods (3%) research (Tang et al., 2021).",
    "By adopting a mixed methods approach in this study of generative AI, qualitative results were able to offer explanatory insight into the quantitative data that were collected (Almalki, 2016).",
    "Providing insights into motivations for change also enables educational leaders to better understand how they may affect change in the use of generative AI by teachers.",
    "A purposefully designed survey was used to collect data, because of the known capacity of survey methods to efficiently harvest standardised responses from a large number of geographically dispersed participants (Nardi, 2018).",
    "Survey methods are often used to conduct high quality research."
  ],
